<p>there is a strange thing that happens to my code: I wrote this function and I call it two times:</p>  <pre><code>uint32_t * findNoises(uint32_t finalBuffer[][16384], uint32_t * jMAxVector){     uint32_t noises[32];     uint32_t sum = 0, nValues = 0;     for(int i = 0; i&lt;32; i++){         for(int j = 0; j&lt;jMAxVector[i]; j++){             if(finalBuffer[i][j]&gt;0){                 sum+=finalBuffer[i][j];                 nValues++;             }         }         if(nValues&gt;0){             noises[i] = (uint32_t)((((double)sum)/((double)nValues))+0.5);         }else{             noises[i] = 0;         }         //cout &lt;&lt; "noise " &lt;&lt; noises[i] &lt;&lt; endl;         sum=0;         nValues=0;     } }; </code></pre>  <p>the first time it goes well, no errors. The second time gives me <code>segmentation fauilt</code>. The strange thing is that if I remove the comment form this line </p>  <pre><code>cout &lt;&lt; "noise " &lt;&lt; noises[i] &lt;&lt; endl; </code></pre>  <p>It goes well also the second time. Why removing the <code>cout</code> makes my code crash? I do not what to keep <code>cout</code>, it is there just for debug.</p>